  "summaries": [
    {
      "id": 515555,
      "category": "team",
      "content": "libcurl's URL API function curl_url_get() offers punycode conversions, to and from IDN. Asking to convert a name that is exactly 256 bytes, libcurl ends up reading outside of a stack based buffer when built to use the macidn IDN backend. The conversion function then fills up the provided buffer exactly - but does not null terminate the string.\n\nThis flaw can lead to stack contents accidentally getting returned as part of the converted string.\n\nFull advisory: https://curl.se/docs/CVE-2024-6874.html",
      "updated_at": "2024-08-23T19:11:31.244Z",
